The paper discusses a method for Bayesian optimization that involves incorporating data from multiple systems with unknown quantitative interrelationships. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), or computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). The paper's focus on Bayesian inference and optimization further supports these potential sub-categories.
